VALUES
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_words_pointing','I’m finding my words',1,true,'need_words_gestures','Finding words everywhere','Your toddler may be pointing, naming familiar things or waiting for you to add the word. Books, songs and everyday object hunts turn these little moments into conversation, helping them connect what they understand with what they are starting to say.','for_your_child','cat_first_word_picture_books','First-word books to point at','First Word Picture Books',1,'Your toddler may point, name or wait for you to say the word. First-word books give easy chances to repeat, pause and add language around animals, body parts and everyday objects, without making speech feel like a test during ordinary family moments.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good gift when it fills a real gap at home.','If you already have something similar, bring it back out and watch whether it still fits the way your toddler plays now before buying more.','First-word picture books','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_words_pointing','I’m finding my words',1,true,'need_words_gestures','Finding words everywhere','Your toddler may be pointing, naming familiar things or waiting for you to add the word. Books, songs and everyday object hunts turn these little moments into conversation, helping them connect what they understand with what they are starting to say.','for_your_child','cat_body_part_books_games','Body-part books and naming games','Body Part Books Games',2,'As body-part pointing starts to appear, dressing, bath time and simple books can become easy naming moments. Asking for eyes, nose or tummy gives your toddler a clear word-to-action link and lets them show understanding before speech is fully clear.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',2,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good gift when it fills a real gap at home.','If you already have something similar, bring it back out and watch whether it still fits the way your toddler plays now before buying more.','Body-part books and naming games','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_words_pointing','I’m finding my words',1,true,'need_words_gestures','Finding words everywhere','Your toddler may be pointing, naming familiar things or waiting for you to add the word. Books, songs and everyday object hunts turn these little moments into conversation, helping them connect what they understand with what they are starting to say.','for_your_child','cat_naming_walks','Words on walks and little hunts','Naming Walks',3,'A buggy trip, walk to the park or lap around the house can become a tiny naming game. Pointing out buses, shoes, dogs and doors helps your toddler connect real things with words, especially when you pause and let them point or answer.','for_your_child','activity','useful_ideas','Useful ideas',1,false,false,false,'Idea',NULL,NULL,NULL,'conor','Save idea','no_shop_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_words_pointing','I’m finding my words',1,true,'need_words_gestures','Finding words everywhere','Your toddler may be pointing, naming familiar things or waiting for you to add the word. Books, songs and everyday object hunts turn these little moments into conversation, helping them connect what they understand with what they are starting to say.','for_your_child','cat_songs_action_games','Songs with actions to copy','Songs Action Games',4,'Songs with actions give your toddler a way to join in before every word is clear. Clapping, pointing, nodding or doing the same action again can support listening, gestures, turn-taking and memory, without making language feel like a lesson in everyday family life.','for_your_child','activity','useful_ideas','Useful ideas',2,false,false,false,'Idea',NULL,NULL,NULL,'conor','Save idea','no_shop_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_words_pointing','I’m finding my words',1,true,'need_words_gestures','Finding words everywhere','Your toddler may be pointing, naming familiar things or waiting for you to add the word. Books, songs and everyday object hunts turn these little moments into conversation, helping them connect what they understand with what they are starting to say.','for_your_child','cat_animal_picture_cards','Animal picture cards to name','Animal Picture Cards',5,'Animal cards give your toddler something clear to point at, name and match to familiar sounds. They work well in short bursts, especially if books are already part of the day and you want one small, portable way to practise words together.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',3,true,true,true,'Good gift','A fresh little language gift if they already have plenty of books.','If you already have animal books, cards are only useful if you want something easier to shuffle, carry or use for quick matching games.','Animal picture cards','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_words_pointing','I’m finding my words',1,true,'need_words_gestures','Finding words everywhere','Your toddler may be pointing, naming familiar things or waiting for you to add the word. Books, songs and everyday object hunts turn these little moments into conversation, helping them connect what they understand with what they are starting to say.','for_your_child','cat_song_rhyme_books','Song and rhyme books','Song Rhyme Books',6,'A rhyme book can make language feel easier to join in with. Repeated words, actions and pauses give your toddler a chance to copy a sound, point to a picture or anticipate what comes next, even if their own words are still emerging.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',4,true,true,true,'Good gift','A lovely gift when you want a book that invites joining in.','If they already have books, look for one with repeated lines, simple actions or a familiar song rather than another general picture book.','Song and rhyme books','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_pretend_copying','I’m copying everyday life',2,true,'need_pretend_copying','Copying everyday life','Your toddler may copy feeding a teddy, stirring a bowl or carrying a little bag. Pretend play gives those watched routines a safe, funny place to practise, while building language, memory, care and early social understanding through scenes they already recognise.','for_your_child','cat_doll_soft_toy_care','A doll or teddy to care for','Doll Soft Toy Care',1,'Your toddler may copy feeding, wiping or cuddling a soft toy after seeing those routines at home. Doll and teddy care gives them a safe way to practise language, sequencing and social understanding, while making everyday care feel funny and familiar.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good gift when it fills a real gap at home.','If you already have something similar, bring it back out and watch whether it still fits the way your toddler plays now before buying more.','Doll or teddy care toy','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_pretend_copying','I’m copying everyday life',2,true,'need_pretend_copying','Copying everyday life','Your toddler may copy feeding a teddy, stirring a bowl or carrying a little bag. Pretend play gives those watched routines a safe, funny place to practise, while building language, memory, care and early social understanding through scenes they already recognise.','for_your_child','cat_toy_cups_spoons','Pretend cups, spoons and food','Toy Cups Spoons',2,'Pretend cups, spoons and food let your toddler copy the routines they watch every day. They can stir, offer a teddy a drink or put food on a plate, giving them a playful way to connect objects, actions and early words.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',2,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good gift when it fills a real gap at home.','If you already have something similar, bring it back out and watch whether it still fits the way your toddler plays now before buying more.','Toy cups, spoons and food','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_pretend_copying','I’m copying everyday life',2,true,'need_pretend_copying','Copying everyday life','Your toddler may copy feeding a teddy, stirring a bowl or carrying a little bag. Pretend play gives those watched routines a safe, funny place to practise, while building language, memory, care and early social understanding through scenes they already recognise.','for_your_child','cat_play_kitchen_household_props','A little kitchen or household props','Play Kitchen Household Props',3,'A small kitchen, pan, whisk or safe household prop can make imitation feel irresistible. Pretend chores and cooking help your toddler practise memory, language and social roles, especially when you join in briefly and give words to what they are doing.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',3,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good gift when it fills a real gap at home.','Borrow or use a simple home version first if you are not sure it will earn repeat use.','Play kitchen or household props','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_pretend_copying','I’m copying everyday life',2,true,'need_pretend_copying','Copying everyday life','Your toddler may copy feeding a teddy, stirring a bowl or carrying a little bag. Pretend play gives those watched routines a safe, funny place to practise, while building language, memory, care and early social understanding through scenes they already recognise.','for_your_child','cat_toddler_bag_carry','A little bag for pretend errands','Toddler Bag Carry',4,'A small bag, basket or pouch lets your toddler copy shopping, nursery drop-off or little errands at home. Carrying objects from one place to another gives pretend play a clear job, while supporting memory, coordination and practical independence in a playful way.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',4,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good gift when it fills a real gap at home.','Borrow or use a simple home version first if you are not sure it will earn repeat use.','Toddler pretend bag','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_pretend_copying','I’m copying everyday life',2,true,'need_pretend_copying','Copying everyday life','Your toddler may copy feeding a teddy, stirring a bowl or carrying a little bag. Pretend play gives those watched routines a safe, funny place to practise, while building language, memory, care and early social understanding through scenes they already recognise.','for_your_child','cat_doctor_visit_books','Doctor and care stories','Doctor Visit Books',5,'Simple doctor, dentist or care books can make unfamiliar routines easier to talk about. Naming the bag, thermometer or waiting room gives your toddler language for real moments, while pretend check-ups with a teddy keep the practice low-pressure before real appointments.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',5,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good gift when it fills a real gap at home.','Borrow or use a simple home version first if you are not sure it will earn repeat use.','Doctor visit board books','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_pretend_copying','I’m copying everyday life',2,true,'need_pretend_copying','Copying everyday life','Your toddler may copy feeding a teddy, stirring a bowl or carrying a little bag. Pretend play gives those watched routines a safe, funny place to practise, while building language, memory, care and early social understanding through scenes they already recognise.','for_your_child','cat_toy_cleaning_set','A little cleaning set','Toy Cleaning Set',6,'If your toddler is starting to copy sweeping, wiping or tidying, a small broom, dustpan or cloth can make that everyday interest easier to join. It is pretend play, movement and routine participation rolled into one simple family-life moment.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',6,true,true,true,'Good gift','A surprisingly thoughtful gift for a toddler who loves copying grown-ups.','You can start with a clean cloth or spare dustpan at home before buying a child-sized set.','Toy cleaning set','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_pretend_copying','I’m copying everyday life',2,true,'need_pretend_copying','Copying everyday life','Your toddler may copy feeding a teddy, stirring a bowl or carrying a little bag. Pretend play gives those watched routines a safe, funny place to practise, while building language, memory, care and early social understanding through scenes they already recognise.','for_your_child','cat_low_table_chair','A low table-and-chair spot','Low Table Chair',7,'A small chair or low table can help when your toddler wants to carry things over, sit down, feed a teddy or copy family routines. It is more of a practical home setup than a classic gift, but it can make everyday pretend play easier to organise.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',7,true,false,true,'Parent buy','A practical family buy rather than a casual gift.','Skip this if you already have a safe low table, child chair or clear floor spot that works for pretend play.','Low toddler table and chair','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_busy_hands','My hands are busy now',3,true,'need_two_handed_control','Busy little hands','Your toddler may keep turning, opening, stacking and posting things to see what happens. These small hand challenges help them practise control, focus and problem-solving, especially when they can repeat the same satisfying action in their own way and see a clear result.','for_your_child','cat_shape_sorters_puzzles','Shape sorters and first puzzles','Shape Sorters Puzzles',1,'A shape sorter or chunky puzzle gives your toddler a clear problem to work through: turn it, test it, try again. The value is in the experimenting, not getting it right quickly, because that practice supports focus, hand control and early problem-solving.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good gift when it fills a real gap at home.','If you already have something similar, bring it back out and watch whether it still fits the way your toddler plays now before buying more.','Shape sorters and first puzzles','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_busy_hands','My hands are busy now',3,true,'need_two_handed_control','Busy little hands','Your toddler may keep turning, opening, stacking and posting things to see what happens. These small hand challenges help them practise control, focus and problem-solving, especially when they can repeat the same satisfying action in their own way and see a clear result.','for_your_child','cat_stacking_pegboard','Pegboards and stacking towers','Stacking Pegboard',2,'Stacking pegs, cups or blocks gives your toddler a satisfying reason to use both hands together. They can place, wobble, knock down and rebuild, practising control, balance, attention and persistence through a game they often want to repeat in everyday family life.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',2,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good gift when it fills a real gap at home.','If you already have something similar, bring it back out and watch whether it still fits the way your toddler plays now before buying more.','Pegboards and stacking towers','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_busy_hands','My hands are busy now',3,true,'need_two_handed_control','Busy little hands','Your toddler may keep turning, opening, stacking and posting things to see what happens. These small hand challenges help them practise control, focus and problem-solving, especially when they can repeat the same satisfying action in their own way and see a clear result.','for_your_child','cat_matching_animals_figures','Chunky animals to match and name','Matching Animals Figures',3,'Chunky animals, figures or matching pictures give your toddler something to hold while you name, sort and compare. Putting the dog with the dog or making the cow say moo can turn matching into language, memory and pretend play in everyday family life.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',3,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good gift when it fills a real gap at home.','Borrow or use a simple home version first if you are not sure it will earn repeat use.','Chunky animal figures','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_busy_hands','My hands are busy now',3,true,'need_two_handed_control','Busy little hands','Your toddler may keep turning, opening, stacking and posting things to see what happens. These small hand challenges help them practise control, focus and problem-solving, especially when they can repeat the same satisfying action in their own way and see a clear result.','for_your_child','cat_posting_drop_boxes','Posting boxes and hidey slots','Posting Drop Boxes',4,'Posting, dropping and tucking objects into a box can hold a toddler’s attention because the action is simple and satisfying. It helps them practise hand control, object permanence and problem-solving, especially when they can open the box and do it again.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',4,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good gift when it fills a real gap at home.','Borrow or use a simple home version first if you are not sure it will earn repeat use.','Posting boxes and drop toys','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_busy_hands','My hands are busy now',3,true,'need_two_handed_control','Busy little hands','Your toddler may keep turning, opening, stacking and posting things to see what happens. These small hand challenges help them practise control, focus and problem-solving, especially when they can repeat the same satisfying action in their own way and see a clear result.','for_your_child','cat_latch_busy_boards','Latches, lids and busy boards','Latch Busy Boards',5,'Latches, lids, switches and flaps can be fascinating at this stage. A toddler-safe busy board or box gives those urges a safer place to practise opening, closing and figuring things out, while building hand strength, focus and persistence in everyday family life.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',5,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good gift when it fills a real gap at home.','Borrow or use a simple home version first if you are not sure it will earn repeat use.','Latch and busy boards','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_busy_hands','My hands are busy now',3,true,'need_hands_problem_solving','Busy little hands','Your toddler may keep turning, opening, stacking and posting things to see what happens. These small hand challenges help them practise control, focus and problem-solving, especially when they can repeat the same satisfying action in their own way and see a clear result.','for_your_child','cat_chunky_crayons','Chunky crayons for first marks','Chunky Crayons',6,'Scribbling may look like random marks, but it gives your toddler a simple way to practise grip, pressure and cause-and-effect. Chunky crayons or washable markers can make those first marks easier to try under close supervision.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',6,true,true,true,'Good gift','A classic small gift if paired with paper or a washable mat.','If you already have crayons, check they are chunky, washable and suitable for supervised toddler use.','Chunky crayons','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_busy_hands','My hands are busy now',3,true,'need_hands_problem_solving','Busy little hands','Your toddler may keep turning, opening, stacking and posting things to see what happens. These small hand challenges help them practise control, focus and problem-solving, especially when they can repeat the same satisfying action in their own way and see a clear result.','for_your_child','cat_water_doodle_mat','Water doodle mat','Water Doodle Mat',7,'A water doodle mat can be a neat way to offer early mark-making when you want something calmer than paints or pens. The interest is simple: they press, swipe, watch a mark appear, then try again.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',7,true,true,true,'Good gift','A fresher art gift with less mess than paints.','Skip this if you already have washable crayons and a setup you are happy to supervise.','Water doodle mat','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_busy_hands','My hands are busy now',3,true,'need_hands_problem_solving','Busy little hands','Your toddler may keep turning, opening, stacking and posting things to see what happens. These small hand challenges help them practise control, focus and problem-solving, especially when they can repeat the same satisfying action in their own way and see a clear result.','for_your_child','cat_stacking_nesting_cups','Stacking and nesting cups','Stacking Nesting Cups',8,'Stacking cups can do more at this age than sit in a toy basket. Your toddler may fill them, hide things under them, nest them together, knock them over or use them in pretend tea. That makes them a useful bridge between hand play, problem-solving and everyday copying.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',8,true,true,true,'Good gift','A classic gift, best if the family does not already have a set.','If you already have stacking cups, bring them back out for hiding, nesting, bath pouring or pretend drinks rather than buying a second set.','Stacking and nesting cups','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_busy_hands','My hands are busy now',3,true,'need_hands_problem_solving','Busy little hands','Your toddler may keep turning, opening, stacking and posting things to see what happens. These small hand challenges help them practise control, focus and problem-solving, especially when they can repeat the same satisfying action in their own way and see a clear result.','for_your_child','cat_chunky_building_sets','Chunky building sets','Chunky Building Sets',9,'Chunky building pieces can suit a toddler who wants to carry, stack, knock down and try again. Choose large, simple pieces that are easy to grip and too big to be a choking hazard, then keep the play short and satisfying.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',9,true,true,true,'Good gift','A solid classic gift if the family needs bigger toddler pieces.','If blocks are already in the house, keep them out before buying another set. The new stage shift is how your toddler uses them.','Chunky building sets','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_move_climb','I’m moving with purpose',4,true,'need_gross_motor','Moving with purpose','Your toddler may be quicker on their feet, more eager to climb and ready to chase a ball across the room. Safe movement games help them practise balance, coordination and confidence, while giving their new energy somewhere useful to go.','for_your_child','cat_soft_graspable_balls','Soft balls to kick and chase','Soft Graspable Balls',1,'A soft ball gives your toddler a simple reason to run, stop, kick, roll and chase. Passing it back and forth also brings social play into movement, helping them practise coordination, balance, attention and taking turns in a very physical way.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good gift when it fills a real gap at home.','If you already have something similar, bring it back out and watch whether it still fits the way your toddler plays now before buying more.','Soft toddler balls','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('19-21m','19–21 months',19,21,true,'ent_cluster_19_21_move_climb','I’m moving with purpose',4,true,'need_gross_motor','Moving with purpose','Your toddler may be quicker on their feet, more eager to climb and ready to chase a ball across the room. Safe movement games help them practise balance, coordination and confidence, while giving their new energy somewhere useful to go.','for_your_child','cat_pull_push_toys','Push-and-pull toys for walking','Pull Push Toys',2,'A push or pull toy can turn walking into a job: take it across the room, bring it back, try again. That little purpose helps your toddler practise balance, direction and coordination while making new movement feel playful and useful.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',2,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good gift when it fills a real gap at home.','If you already have something similar, bring it back out and watch whether it still fits the way your toddler plays now before buying more.','Push and pull toys','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
